  "title": "Technician (Crane)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Execute maintenance, inspection, repair, and installation tasks for cranes, hoists, and other material handling equipment.</li>\n  <li>Carry out preventive maintenance, inspections, and repairs at multiple customer sites.</li>\n  <li>Conduct customer assessments, document findings, and provide recommendations for improvements or additional services.</li>\n  <li>Leverage company digital tools to manage work orders and communicate with customers effectively.</li>\n  <li>Identify potential sales opportunities and suggest performance or safety enhancements.</li>\n  <li>Ensure proper upkeep of company vehicles, tools, and equipment.</li>\n  <li>Comply with all safety regulations and customer-specific requirements.</li>\n  <li>Report hazards, incidents, and safety observations in accordance with company protocols.</li>\n  <li>Perform on-site work in strict adherence to EHS (Environment, Health, and Safety) standards and procedures.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma / NITEC in Electrical or Mechanical with completion of apprenticeship</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years' experience in relevant industries</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd | EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22110981| EA Personnel Name: Law Mei Fong</p>",
